$$\frac{. \overline{7} }{. \overline{8} } = \frac{7}{9} \cdot \frac{9}{8}$$

The $9$ in the numerator and denominator cancels out, leaving us with:

$$\frac{. \overline{7} }{. \overline{8} } = \frac{7}{8}$$

